<REFENTRY ID="baselib-gets"> <REFMETA>
<REFENTRYTITLE>gets</REFENTRYTITLE>
<REFMISCINFO>Base Libraries</REFMISCINFO>
</REFMETA>
<REFNAMEDIV>
<REFNAME>gets</REFNAME>
<REFPURPOSE>
get a line of input (deprecated)
</REFPURPOSE>
</REFNAMEDIV>
<REFSECT1>
<TITLE>Description
</TITLE>
<para>
The gets function is expected to disappear from a future version
of the LSB; applications should call fgets instead.<footnote><para>
Programs which use gets are almost always vulnerable to overflowing
the buffer supplied to gets.
</para></footnote>
</para>
<para>
The gets function is as specified in the Single UNIX Specification.
</para>
</REFSECT1>
</REFENTRY>
